                        <collation>
                           <p>
                              
                              
                              
                              Folios 16 to 235 form 22 complete quires of 10 leaves each, signed with hebrew letters on the last page and also marked by catchwords.
                              
                              
                              
                              Folios 7 to 15 are the remaining leaves of the second quire.
                              
                              
                              
                              Folios 1 to 6 have been added later (probably in 16th century) to supply the deficiency at the beginnig.
                              
                              
                              
                              Folding of folios 236 to 242 is uncertain.
                           
                           
                           
                           
                              
                              
                              
                              Only four pages are extant.
                           
                           
                           
                           </p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 1 2 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 29 37 28;
                                                  written lines: 28 36 28; Each of the books ends with several rhymed lines.The last line of text is written under the last ruled line.Visible ruling with hard-point.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
